{
  "texts": [
    "We can define the AdS 3 twistors asZ I = ξ α η α.The incidence relation is thenξ α = (X T) αβ η β,which defines the relationship between the AdS 3 spacetime and its twistor space.",
    "At the boundary, we have the condition X 2 = 0 and soX αβ ξ β = (X 2) α β η β = 0.Thus the incidence relation on the boundary becomes X αβ ξ β = 0, which may be written asξ -+ γξ + = 0.",
    "(2.14)Defining the twistor on the boundary CP 1 as z α = ξ α, we see that this is an incidence relation for the twistor on the boundary.",
    "Moreover, in light of the scaling between ξ α and η α, it is natural to interpret w α = η α as the dual twistor for the boundary theory, giving the identificationZ I = z α w α ∈ CP 1 × CP 1.12 We adopt notation similar to [19,22] where an element of Euclidean AdS3 is given by g = (g αβ) =e γt + e -2Φt 3 e -γt -, wheret+ = 0 1 0 0, t-= 0 0 -1 0, t3 = 1 2 1 0 0 -1, satisfying the algebra [t+, t-] = -2t3, [t3, t±] = ±t±.",
    "JHEP04(2024)048Thus we see that Z I, a twistor of AdS 3, is simultaneously the ambitwistor of the boundary [42]."
  ]
}